,Recommended,310890,17042889,"Posted: 14 July, 2015",all,Syn✯vion,"I first bought this game after playing the original Breach & Clear.  I must say I was amazed at how fun Deadline is.  Buying it when it was in the early stages of development and constantly weaving through squads of characters to kill everything in my path was so satisfying.  The gameplay is simple & tactical.  Point & Click and issue commands in command mode or go knee deep just using your mouse and keyboard to travel around with your squad. Mind you, you can alternate between command and normal mode at anytime.  Different classes with different skills that you can use to your advantage in combat.  Different weapons you can use as well (SMG, Shotgun, AR, Grenades) to your liking and style of your squad.  What really impresses me is how the devs actually work with the community to help with updates and bugs.  A dedicated group for an underhyped game.  Overall Deadline is a great buy if you like tatical, military, zombie, strategy, top-down combat style games.  Especially if you liked the original Breach & Clear."
