76561197970722928,Not Recommended,310890,30526567,Posted: 15 March,all,U_R_Wormfood,"First I’d like to say that I really enjoyed the original Breach and Clear. Having said that, Deadline Rebirth is a major step backwards. Many of things that worked well in the original seem horribly broken in this game. The pathing, which is a complete necessity in this type of game to get your soldiers to the proper positions and do their job, only works about 30% of the time. Any time they need to path around objects they get stuck, run in circles, then give up trying, which often leaves your other soldiers unprotected, and the soldier you were trying to move exposed and out of cover. Being able to “stack” commands that will be executed in order ends up feeling clunky, because if you try to quickly adapt to the situation as it develops, if the soldier hasn’t executed their first command, you have to select each one and cancel that command to give them a new one.In general, I feel like most of the strategy available in the first game, which was true turn-based strategy, has been lost in this game by trying to make it more fluid using the time control system. The fact that the pathing is so bad makes you want to avoid the command view altogether and just control your soldier in the top-down shooter mode. I do not recommend this game."
