,Recommended,310890,15454710,"Posted: 19 April, 2015",all,Hanosandy,"A good tactical top down game.  Controls at times are confusing and don't work.  The vertical parts of levels are often times hard to recognize from one another.  Inventory system is at times unclear.  This is an early access game currently and needs work - but the framework in place has all the great markers of a great game to come.  Weapons and tactics vary widely enough to provide plenty of options of approach.  The class based squad selection reminds me a lot of the old Rainbow Six games.  The seperate abilities available to each class are varied and provide a useful balance.  The enemy AI is unintelligent, but they are zombies what do you expect them to be, ...smart?  Overall I can recommend getting into this early access if helping this game become a a reality in the tactical top down genre is a good thing to you.  While I have already experienced some bugs within an  hour of gameplay, you can tell this is building up to be a good game.  There ARE human enemies, but consider this primarily a game versus zombies."
