76561198010359952,Recommended,310890,17196677,"Posted: 23 July, 2015",all,fightingcrow60,"This game is really good, especially considering the on-sale price of only $14. It is a great squad-based tactical with a satisfying amount of character development options that are not overly complex. It is easy to quickly decide how to assign skill points and customize weapons/gear. You don't feel like you have to obsess over char dev as much as Wasteland 2 (for example).  The musical score is awesome - really helps develop the post-apoc theme and suspense without being a repetitive distraction. The layout of the world feels a little linear rather than sandbox, but I'm only 6 hours in. Thats ok for me because I like having some guidance/direction while still being able to make my own choices on where to explore and what quests to accept. I wish I could customize the controls to my own personal preferences, but at least they assigned all the game functions to keys on the left side of the keyboard, so you don't have to constantly jump from one side to the other. The AI seems a little on the easy side...most of the time my squad kills all enemies before they even get close enough to do any damage. My team just hit level 4, so I am looking for the threat of actually dying to increase as I progress through the campaign. If a difficulty setting exists, I have not found it. The game is great in small doses, but I think I could easily spend a whole day on it without getting bored. So far, the only role-specific special ability I have used is the explosive expert's satchel charge which is really cool; maybe the other squad-members abilities will become more relevant/necessary later on."
