76561198034482587,Recommended,310890,19547672,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,The Witcher,"It's an awesome game, but not the game I would recommend to everyone.Following its predecessor, I personally think that Deadline was able to fill in the gaps in gameplay that was lacking in the original Breach and Clear. With the new real-time command mode, you really feel that you are in control over the squad. To the movements, which enemy to attack, what to do at that certain time, the flexibility is fantastic. It's easy to familiarize yourself with the mechanics of the game, but the game itself isn't quite a walk in the park. Even though you are facing melee zombies (for the most part, but you will encounter armed bandits), the game doesn't let you take it easy. You still have to think your actions through, and make sure you don't make unforced errors, as at times, it can turn the tides to their favor. The mix of RTS, top-down shooter, and an RPG-esque campaign feels something really fresh.Deadline's gameplay is certainly fun. With a mix of different classes, all with their respective specialties, the gameplay becomes very satisfying when they get used properly, and the plans comes together. Story-wise, the plot isn't anything that special, but not horrible to the point that it ruins the game. On terms of replayability, although you can only control a 4-man squad (there are 6 classes overall), you can replay the game and try using different combinations of classes as the gameplay can greatly change, however the downside is that the plot isn't really something that much replayable. However, you can play dungeons, which is great if you're more on gameplay than going for the plot.Overall, Deadline is a great sucessor to the original Breach and Clear (which was great as well) although there were ocassional bugs, most of have been dealt with on the recent patches. As much as I recommend it, I suggest that you buy it on sale because it is a bit overpriced.I give the game an 7.8/10. Even though the game has some downsides, I think it makes up for it with its awesome gameplay.+Excellent gameplay+Very rewarding*graphics isn't bad, but isn't that great either.-Plot isn't anything that special-low replayability (you can play on dungeons though)-a 'lil bit expensive"
