,Recommended,310890,26723684,"Posted: 20 November, 2016",all,TurboLento,"I feel like the recent reviews have been very unfair and incomplete, or we've been playing a different game.This game mixes missions in ""real time with pause"" squad tactics with an open world with loot RPG (where you explore the world, finding new gear or materials to upgrade your current gear). The open world and RPG factors gives this new approach an interesting flow of exploration, loot gathering, and then entering missions where tactics become very important. You get 4 soldiers in your squad which feels more than enough.As your soldiers level up, they gain skill points that you can use to upgrade their skills. Even though they start with pre defined classes, you're allowed to pick skills from any other class if you wish, effectively allowing multi-classing and many options of customizing your soldiers.It's very streamlined, the amount of interaction options is simple but allows for good tactics (run to spot ignoring fire, strafe to spot firing in assigned direction, auto fire or hold fire, switch to side weapon, reload, use skill or use inventory item). I played with gamepad, to which it has full support, and it's very comfortable doing so (in a genre which rarely pays attention to gamepad play, as you'll well know if you've bought other games of the genre).The introduction of zombies brings a new avenue of tactics, where it becomes mostly about quick repositioning, controlling your troop spacing, keeping obstacles between you and them, keeping your distance to the fast incoming waves of enemies, and ammo/reload management, instead of the more cover/flanking approach to the enemy human encounters. The zombie scenario also allows for the story of a small squad roaming a dangerous open world, needing to scavenge to upgrade your gear, etc.Beside zombies, you'll also face human enemies with guns, and they are very accurate and lethal, demanding good tactics management from you. You'll have to frequently pull back your soldiers and spend some time looking at your inventory, considering your options of flashbangs, smoke grenades, etc, and also consider your soldier specific skills to figure out how to approach each scenario.The real time with pause makes missions have a fun quick pace, especially with the zombie missions, a nice mix of action and strategy.During my 3 hours of play, I came across absolutely ZERO bugs.A solid and refreshing entry in the strategy tactics games scene."
