76561198038091775,Recommended,310890,23335758,"Posted: 1 June, 2016",all,Amor Sin,"------Normally don\'t write reviews this long, if you want a summary go to the bottom.One of the games I wish had a mixed button instead of yes or noSo I never played the orignal breach and clear, but let me be clear, I enjoy this game immensly despite its various flaws.Before getting this game, watche lets plays, gameplay e.t.c.This is a very niche based game. You will either enjoy it or you won\'t.With that said lets jump inYoure basically a squad of special forces trying to get stuff did.You fight zombies, special zombies MUTANT ZOMBIES I DERSAY.You command a squad of four people, there are five classes (6?) I believe. Each class has its own signature weapon, Assault Rifles, LMG\'s, Shotguns, Snipers and submachine guns.Each class has roughly 3-5 active abilitites that let them do stuff.A lot of times when dealing with enemies its pretty rock paper spock lizard demon, I.E there are multiple ways to deal with them. BUT that doesn't stop you from branching into other classes skill tree's or their weapons. Infact you can build your team however you want, Example: Four demolitionst with LMG's, suppression and medic skills.There is real time that lets you run and gun and a tactical mode. Tactical mode lets you pause, issue orders, move your squad e.t.c Just a piece of advice, you can change it from holding down the key to keep it running to a toggle, just learned this five minutes ago.In addition, while the storyline is somewhat linear, espically the begining, they have multiple procedural generated dungeons for funsies.Also, if you do get this game, make sure to right click on the .exe in the steamfiles and make sure you are using your dedicated graphics card not your integrated. My biggest turn off was for a while I couldn\'t play this as it would run at 5fps, I know its horrible. I learned my Nividia card didn\'t always activate thanks to Mordheim, and now I sit at a steady 30-45, again not the best but its an improvement.Overall I love this game, its quaint, its unique, its a specific niche game that I enjoy because its simplistic nature. I also love it cause not many games give you the real time/pause tactical squad based gameplay, Red Solstice single player being my other favorite of this genre.Just to summarize, watch lets plays, know that this is a specific niche game, it is not for everyone, bugs and issues do exist, and a few can be personally fixed."
